HEADWORD: Exestuate
<hw>Ex*es"tu*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exaestuatus</ets>,p. p. of <ets>exaestuare</ets> to boil up. See
<er>Estuate</er>.]</ety> <def>To be agitated; to boil up; to
effervesce.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exestuation</ent>⟦br⟧
